Done. I executed all 25 iterations following the brief's protocol and emitted both required outputs:

- `transcript.json` — schema-validated, 25 iterations, 75 hypotheses, 75 analyses (chi-square, univariable & multivariable logistic, treatment-by-biomarker interaction tests). Each analysis includes signed `effect_estimate`, `p_value`, and `significant`.
- `analysis_summary.txt` — narrative synthesis grouped by theme (prognostic markers, treatments, predictive interactions, lab/clinical predictors, multivariable models, demographics/equity, composites, three-way effects) with overall conclusions.

Headline findings in this cohort (n=50,000, ORR 16.9%):
- ECOG PS dominates (logOR -0.38, p≈10⁻⁹⁷); a coherent frailty/inflammation cluster (low albumin, high CRP, weight loss, higher blast %, higher WBC) all support response prediction.
- IDH1 mutation is associated with +5.6 pp ORR — but ivosidenib does NOT mediate this; IDH1+ patients on ivosidenib had LOWER ORR (17.4% vs 22.5%, interaction p=0.027). Targeted-therapy receipt was essentially independent of biomarker status.
- Classic predictive pairings (midostaurin/gilteritinib×FLT3, enasidenib×IDH2, ven+aza×TP53) were null.
- Venetoclax+azacitidine showed a small adjusted benefit (logOR +0.056, p=0.022) and a positive interaction with unfit_for_intensive (+1.6 pp; beat 7+3 head-to-head in unfit by 1.7 pp, p=0.025).
- TP53/complex karyotype/secondary AML showed no marginal ORR effect.
- Equity: no significant treatment-receipt disparities by race or insurance; small adjusted residual lower ORR for race='black' vs white (p=0.0035).
